        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 30 at 9:15PM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 915 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles southeast of Muddy Creek WMA, or 13 miles northeast of Mount
Ida, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hot Springs...                    Hot Springs Village...
Mountain Pine...                  Jessieville...
Lake Ouachita State Park...       Hot Springs National Park...
Avant...                          Mt Tabor...
Fannie...                         Mountain Valley...
Lena Landing Rec Area...          Hamilton...
Hollis...                         Onyx...
Story...                          Washita...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
